{"lemma":"مَظْلِمَةٌ","slug":"مَظْلِمَةٌ","root":"ظ.ل.م","root_slug":"ظ-ل-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ظ-ل-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27664"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B8%D9%92%D9%84%D9%90%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ظَلَمَ (ẓalama) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"feminine singular of مُظْلِم (muẓlim)","tags":["feminine","form-of","singular"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27664","headword_ar":"مَظْلِمَةٌ","root":"Zlm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maZolamapN","text_ar":"مَظْلَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, near the beginning. ―         -b2-  Also the former, (T, S, M, Mgh, Msb, K,) and the latter likewise, mentioned by Ibn-Málik and ISd and IKtt, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maZolumapN","text_ar":"مَظْلُمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is disallowed"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1923},{"kind":"text","text":"by several but mentioned on the authority of Fr, and all three are mentioned in the Towsheeh and in copies of the S, (MF, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZulaAmapN","text_ar":"ظُلَامَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, Mgh, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaliymapN","text_ar":"ظَلِيمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing of which one has been defrauded;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K; [in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taZal~amahu","text_ar":"تَظَلَّمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuZul~imahu","text_ar":"تُظُلِّمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":";])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing of which thou hast been defrauded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aal~atiY","text_ar":"اَلَّتِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZulimotahaA","text_ar":"ظُلِمْتَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", T,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that thou demandest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taTolubuhu","text_ar":"تَطْلُبُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the possession of the wrongdoer;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, Msb;) a term for"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that has been taken from thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S; [thus, as is said in the M, the first is expl. by Sb;])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due, that has been taken from one wrongfully:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Mgh:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mZlmp","text_ar":"مظلمة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maZaAlimu","text_ar":"مَظَالِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh, TA.) In the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomu AlmaZaAlimi","text_ar":"يَوْمُ المَظَالِمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The day"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the demand"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of things wrongfully taken,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and particularly applied to the great day of judgment,] the prefixed noun [i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Talabi","text_ar":"طَلَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is suppressed. (Mgh.) [Respecting the office termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aZaru","text_ar":"النَّظَرُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY AlmaZaAlimi","text_ar":"فِى المَظَالِمِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The examination into wrongful exactions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"see De Sacy's Chrest. Ar., see. ed., i. 132.]"}],"source_refs":["T","S","M","Mgh","Msb","K","MF","TA","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}